1 Download Ubuntu Server Using https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Download Ubuntu Server Iso
3 Flash Usb To Etcher Ventoy Or Rufus
4 Setup Ubuntu Server
  If You See Choose The type of installation
  Choose Ubuntu Server (minimized) Because 
  Ubuntu Server Minimized is highly lightweight, specifically designed to be roughly 50% smaller in disk size than the standard server image and offers faster boot times.
  It removes unnecessary packages, reduces the security attack surface, and provides a bare-bones base ideal for cloud deployments
5 You May Stop The Services Of Snap
  sudo systemctl stop snapd
  sudo systemctl disable snapd

6 Purge Snapd (Recommended For Older Hardware Or Any Slow Hardware)
  sudo apt purge snapd

7 Clean Up Leftover Directories
  rm -rf ~/snap
  sudo rm -rf /var/snap /var/lib/snapd /var/cache/snapd

8 Reboot
  sudo reboot

9 System Updates: Ubuntu may reinstall Snapd during major upgrades. To prevent this, you can block Snapd from being reinstalled:
  sudo apt-mark hold snapd

10 sudo apt update
   sudo apt install twm ubuntu-wallpapers -y

11 sudo apt install lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter

12 sudo systemctl enable lightdm
   sudo systemctl start lightdm

13 Have Fun And Start Using It
